title: Men's NCAA tournament: Live updates, highlights, analysis from Day 1
author: ESPN

title: McNeese scripts 'biggest day' in upset of Clemson
description: McNeese coach Will Wade and his boom box-toting manager are moving on in March Madness after the 12th-seeded Cowboys held off No. 5 seed Clemson on Thursday in the first bracket buster of the NCAA tournament.
author: Pete Thamel and Mike Reiss

title: 'Scotland's great survivor Hanley basks in battle'
description: Grant Hanley has been written off, left out and cast aside. But the 33-year-old was there again when Scotland needed him, writes Tom English.

title: England captain Kane feels he is 'taken for granted'
description: England captain Harry Kane says he is "taken for granted" and feels people have become "bored" of his goalscoring record.

title: Tuchel: England were afraid at the Euros
description: Thomas Tuchel aims to bring back the excitement for England after saying their players were weighed down by pressure and "playing not to lose" at the Euros.

title: Kane: I was surprised when Tuchel got England job
description: Harry Kane has admitted he was "surprised" when Thomas Tuchel was named England head coach but said the German brings more "energy and enthusiasm" to the role than predecessor Gareth Southgate.

title: Braden Fiske calls Cooper Kupp 'one of the greatest humans' he's been around
description: Braden Fiske enjoyed his one season playing with Cooper Kupp.

title: Golden State Warriors jersey history - No. 8 - Nemanja Nedovic (2013-14)
description: During his time suiting up for the Warriors, Nedovic wore only jersey No. 8 and put up 1.1 points per game.
